ional Arts Festival The Folk Research Centre has been prominent part Lucian cultural research since 1973 and has also published the journal Lucian Kaiso devoted Lucian calypso since 1990 The islands calypso traditions are also celebrated the annual kaiposium kaiso symposium held since 1987 The islands music industry remains littleknown internationally and small economic importance The government Saint Lucia has worked with the OECS promote the regional music industry through intellectual property law and sponsoring festivals and other activities The most important festival modern Lucian culture the Jounen Kwyl International Creole Day held annually October since 1983 The Jounen Kwyl sponsored the Bannzil Kwyl international organization Lucian activities are run the Folk Research Centre conjunction with the National Research and Development Foundation and the Mouvman Kwyl Sent Lisi Lucia Creole Movement Lucian law protects the owners intellectual property such songwriters through the Copyright Act 1995 copyrights are administered the Hewanorra Musical Society There also Saint Lucia Jazz Festival that major attraction and wellknown part the local music scene has been annual event for fifteen years and has hosted variety jazz stars addition local talent The 2005 festival was boost for the local music industry netting million The Festival sponsored number corporations and groups perhaps most significantly BET Music part the curriculum public schools Saint Lucia has long been taught younger grade levels but was only introduced secondary education 1999 Primary education Saint Lucia music and other artistic education commonly used incidentally teaching other subjects for special occasions About the islands schools engage general music education while others spent more time general group singing choir recorder ensemble performance 2003 string program was instituted for primary students About schools teach music the lower secondary level Many the schools that not normally instruct music may offer volunteer clubs other more informal opportunities for musical enrichment Many Lucian schools have formed ensembles most commonly wind ensemble schools steelpan band combo group The public education field has also collaborated with the Saint Lucia School Music form the National Youth Choir String Orchestra and Secondary Schools Wind Ensemble The governmental Ministry Education also sponsors number festivals and musical special events both for the benefit all students and the enrichment the musicallygifted among them The Saint Lucia School Music independent institute music education that has two branches the island one the north and one the south was established 1987 and has student body around four hundred students The Schools professed goal provide music education all levels offer community opportunities for musical enrichment facilitate the training and professional development educators and establish the school musical resource There also notable music Education Centre operated vocal group from the fishing village Anse Raye this Centre provides music education opportunities for gifted and underprivileged children from across the island 